cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sequence modeling tasks in text and speech processing. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it mentions speech processing tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a mechanism to improve the performance of the system. Finally, it could also be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the imbalance between certain token pairs in the sequence.
